[Sheffield is a city and metropolitan borough in South Yorkshire, England. The population of the City of Sheffield is 551 800 (2011 census), and it is one of the 8 largest regional English cities that make up the Core Cities Group. Sheffield is the 3rd largest English district by population. Sheffield can be located in the centre of the map of England at: http://www.itraveluk.co.uk/maps/england.html. The number of measles cases in this part of England (the Yorkshire and Humber area) has been reduced, but a small number of cases continue to be recorded every month. - Mod.CP

