Date: Fri 16 Aug 2013
Source: BBCNews north West Wales [edited]
http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-north-west-wales-23722502


There is a warning that up to 30 000 children in Wales still need urgent protection against measles, despite the epidemic in the Swansea area being brought under control. The Welsh assembly's health committee said there could be "no room for complacency between outbreaks."

