[7] Canada (Ontario)
Date: Sat 16 Aug 2013
Source: News Talk 11290 [edited]
http://www.cjbk.com/LocalNews/story.aspx?ID=2025951


Officials are pleading with the public to check their immunisation records after the 2nd lab-confirmed case of measles. A child, under the age of one, is the 2nd person within a month to test positive for the disease; however, officials don't think the 2 are connected.

Anyone who may have visited Food Basics on Dundas St in Woodstock on 9 Aug 2013 between 6:45 p.m. and 9 p.m. should check their immunization record, or contact a health care professional if they are experiencing symptoms of measles. Symptoms are very similar to the flu, including fever, runny nose, red blotchy spots, drowsiness and irritability among other things.

--
